Key Match Events: DeMar DeRozan scored nine of his game-high 30 points in the second overtime, helping the Sacramento Kings outlast the Miami Heat 123-118.
Domantas Sabonis recorded a triple-double with 21 points, 18 rebounds, and 11 assists.
Jaime Jaquez Jr. also notched a triple-double with 10 assists and 12 rebounds, along with five steals.
Neither team scored in the final 50 seconds of regulation, with missed shots from Tyler Herro and DeMar DeRozan.
Haywood Highsmith blocked a Malik Monk jumper with 4.8 seconds left in the first overtime.
Keon Ellis was fouled with nine-tenths of a second left in the first overtime but made only one of two free throws, sending the game to a second overtime.
